ethical life--family, civil society, and the state--and provide the arena of a crucial third kind of freedom, which Honneth calls "communicative" freedom. A society is just only if it gives all of its members sufficient and equal opportunity to realize communicative freedom as well as personal and moral freedom.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 0aEthics. 0aLawxPhilosophy. 0aNatural law. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Modern.2bisacsh  aAristotle.  aHegel and Modern Society (Taylor).  aMarxism.  aPiaget, Jean.  aRousseau, Jean-Jacques.  aTaylor, Charles.  aWalzer, Michael.  aWittgenstein, Ludwig.  aaction theory.  abasic goods.  aburdens.  acapitalism.  acategorical imperative.  acivic duties.  acommunitarianism.  aconstitutional patriotism.  aconstructivism.  acorporation/community.  ademocratic will.  adiagnosis of the age.  aduty.  aeducation.  aethics.  afeelings.  afriendship.  aindeterminacy, suffering from.  aindividualism’s threat.  ainterests.  aintersubjectivity, repression of.  alanguage games.  alegal freedom.  aliberalism.  aliberation.  amarket-mediated circulation.  amarriage.  amoral relativism.  aobject relations.  aobjective spirit.  aoccupational groups.  aphilosophical therapy.  apsychoanalytic theory.  areligion.  arestraint.  aromantic individualism.  aromantic subjectivity.  asuffering, generally.  atrust.  auniversal rights as basic goods.  avacuity.  avolitions, first- vs. second-order.  awomen’s roles.1 aLöb, Ladislaus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044250208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-